# Adjust Haptic Feedback Timing

## Goal
Make the haptic feedback for "slide to save" occur earlier in the swipe gesture.

## Proposed Changes
### [lib/widgets/swipe_to_save_widget.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/widgets/swipe_to_save_widget.dart)
- [MODIFY] Change the haptic feedback triggering threshold in [_onDragUpdate](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/widgets/swipe_to_save_widget.dart#42-55) from `0.8` (80%) to `0.5` (50%).

```dart
    // Haptic feedback intensity increases as you slide
    if (_dragValue > (_maxWidth - _height) * 0.5) { // Changed from 0.8
      HapticFeedback.lightImpact();
    }
```

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
- Run the app on a physical device (if available to the user) or simulator.
- Use the "slide to save" feature.
- Verify that haptic feedback starts feeling "buzzy" or active earlier in the drag motion than before.
